                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13277199" author="rgauss" created="Wed, 16 May 2012 23:08:18 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Apply to tika-core.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13277215" author="gagravarr" created="Wed, 16 May 2012 23:38:49 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, applied (with a few extra JavaDoc bits) in r1339404.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s good to finally make clear which bits of metadata we try to ensure are consistent across formats, and which ones will be file type specific. That way, external consumers who need format specific details know which ones they are, while general users can be sure that the metadata they&apos;re looking at is a consistent one&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13278006" author="rgauss" created="Thu, 17 May 2012 18:40:07 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Changes to call properties defined in the new TikaCoreProperties class rather than the now deprecated Metadata string keys.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13278130" author="gagravarr" created="Thu, 17 May 2012 20:23:09 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Core patch applied in r1339804, thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13278196" author="gagravarr" created="Thu, 17 May 2012 21:06:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Parsers patch applied in r1339833, that was an epic patch, thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13278507" author="gagravarr" created="Fri, 18 May 2012 03:11:01 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;As of r1339868 we now have most of a core set of Properties defined, including aliases for backwards compatibility (until Tika 2.0 when we can tidy things up!)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I there are probably still a few more common properties we should probably bring across (including converting to Properties with Prefixes as needed). These would be from both interfaces we&apos;ve not yet worked on, as well as possibly a few more from MSOffice (would need converting to Office in the process if so). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With that in mind, I&apos;ll leave this issue open for now, until we finish the review and sort these additional properties out.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14343301" author="tpalsulich" created="Mon, 2 Mar 2015 16:00:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hey Nick. Is this another issue we&apos;ll touch up for 2.0?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14343331" author="gagravarr" created="Mon, 2 Mar 2015 16:22:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yup, come Tika 2.0 we can remove the backwards compatible aliases, remove the importing of the various core properties onto Metadata, convert any remaining String ones to Properties etc!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
